Privacy Policy for LearnQuest AI
Effective Date: April 29, 2025

LearnQuest AI ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application.

1. Information We Collect
Personal Information: When you sign up or log in (via Google or email), we collect your email address and related credentials.

User Content: If you upload images or use the camera, we process them locally or in the cloud to extract text (OCR), but we do not store the images.

Usage Data: We collect anonymous usage statistics, device information, and error logs to improve app performance.

2. How We Use Your Information
To provide AI-driven educational assistance.

To personalize your experience and improve our services.

To respond to user inquiries and provide support.

3. Sharing of Information
We do not sell or rent your personal data.

We may share minimal data with trusted service providers (e.g., Firebase, OpenAI) to deliver core functionality.

We comply with lawful requests, such as court orders or government regulations.

4. Data Security
We use industry-standard encryption and security practices to protect your data.

5. Childrenâ€™s Privacy
LearnQuest AI is intended for users aged 13 and above. We do not knowingly collect data from children under 13.

6. Your Rights
You may access, modify, or delete your data by contacting us at [your support email].

7. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy. Changes will be posted in the app.
